                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <pb n="232"/> FILBY. Three 3 membranes sewn together, viz.: 
               (a) Plea concerning the bequest by 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Fyleby</surname>
                        </persName> of land and advowson of the
               church of <placeName role="church" key="place_104296">Filby</placeName>, to his bastard son at the instigation of
               <persName>
                           <forename>Wauter</forename> de <surname>Fyleby</surname>
                        </persName>, to the disinheritance of the
               right heirs of the said Robert. [<origDate when="1333" precision="low">c. 1333</origDate>]
               
               Noted by Le Neve 'Posted'
               </p>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
               (b)
               Memorandum of the claim and descent of a moiety of the manor of <placeName type="manor" key="place_104047">Easthall
               in Rameseye</placeName>, through <persName>
                           <forename>Joan</forename> de <surname>Philby</surname>
                        </persName>, one of the
               daughters of <persName>
                           <forename>R.</forename>(?) de <surname>Philby</surname>
                        </persName> to Olbech [Holbech]
               and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Berkyng</surname>
                        </persName>. <origDate notAfter="1410" notBefore="1390" cert="low">[c. 1400?]</origDate>
                
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
               (c) Memorandum of the sale of the lands and tenements of 
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Berkyng</surname>
                        </persName> in
               <placeName key="place_104614">Wanlysworde</placeName> near London, by 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Clement</forename> de <surname>Brethenam</surname>
                        </persName>, ... <!-- CHK --> of John de Berkyng, for Â£40, of which the
               said John has received 26 marks. 
               . </p>
                  </msItem>
